    <item>
      <title>Wherever The Wind Takes Me</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/2025/01-08-wherever-the-wind-takes-me/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 08 Jan 2025 22:32:00 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/2025/01-08-wherever-the-wind-takes-me/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Here&amp;rsquo;s a video of me performing the piece:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;    &lt;div style=&#34;position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.25%; height: 0; overflow: hidden;&#34;&gt;&#xA;      &lt;iframe allow=&#34;accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share&#34; allowfullscreen=&#34;allowfullscreen&#34; loading=&#34;eager&#34; referrerpolicy=&#34;strict-origin-when-cross-origin&#34; src=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/embed/t-HdAvsmOeM?autoplay=0&amp;amp;controls=1&amp;amp;end=0&amp;amp;loop=0&amp;amp;mute=0&amp;amp;start=0&#34; style=&#34;position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; border:0;&#34; title=&#34;YouTube video&#34;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Consider supporting me via BandCamp:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;iframe scrolling=&#34;no&#34; style=&#34;border: 0;width: 100%;height: 50px;&#34; src=&#34;https://bandcamp.com/band_follow_button_deluxe/3121264827&#34;&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/posts/2025/01-08-wherever-the-wind-takes-me/org-babel-lilypond-exports/feature-cover-thumbnail-2025-01-08.png&#34;&#xA;    alt=&#34;The motif of the piece in musical notation.&#34;&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;&#xA;      &lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;figure-number&#34;&gt;Figure 1: &lt;/span&gt;Motif of Wherever the Wind Takes Me&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In retrospect,&#xA;I hear the piece as modal in nature&#xA;specifically because of the accidentals in certain harmonies.&#xA;I might refer to some of the sequences later, so here they are:&#xA;a 2-up-3-down sequence closes the first half of the piece;&#xA;a descending-fifths sequence &amp;ldquo;masked&amp;rdquo; with&#xA;a smooth descending bass line in the latter half;&#xA;and also, I seem to have played cascading romanescas&#xA;(falling bass variants) in the latter half.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
